install bcryptjs library to save passwords as encrypted
npm install bcryptjs


what will happen when a user successfully logs in - we need to store session state
either we can use sessions i.e. express-session stored in redis (connect-redis)
or JWT tokens

PS D:\devops\5-CKA\docker_redis> npm install redis connect-redis express-session


from npmjs.com for connect-redis

API
Full setup using redis package:

        import RedisStore from "connect-redis"
        import session from "express-session"
        import {createClient} from "redis"

        // Initialize client.
        let redisClient = createClient()
        redisClient.connect().catch(console.error)

        // Initialize store.
        let redisStore = new RedisStore({
        client: redisClient,
        prefix: "myapp:",
        })

        // Initialize sesssion storage.
        app.use(
        session({
            store: redisStore,
            resave: false, // required: force lightweight session keep alive (touch)
            saveUninitialized: false, // recommended: only save session when data exists
            secret: "keyboard cat",
        })
        )